			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	We have an open position for a Senior Analyst to join our core team&#39;s research activities.</p>
<p>
	Qualifications<br />
	Ideal candidates will have 3-5 years working experience as an analyst or researcher at a handset manufacturer, network operator or industry analysis firm. We&lsquo;re also looking for a deep understanding of mobile platforms and their evolution. If you have spent time following mobile software then you &lsquo;ll know how complex and fast-moving this industry is.</p>
<p>
	Responsibilities<br />
	- Research new market sectors, interview vendors and write up major VisionMobile reports like Developer Economics.<br />
	- Form a core part of our research service team.<br />
	- Take key concepts from our Mobile Innovation Economics workshops, and develop into blog articles.<br />
	- Edit contributions to the blog (from 3rd parties or VisionMobile team).<br />
	- Present at major conferences on VisionMobile research topics.<br />
	- Get involved as a researcher in customer projects, from voice innovation to developer segmentation.<br />
	- Manage briefings with vendors on key events or around key reports.</p>
<p>
	Skills<br />
	- Good understanding of the mobile industry, having previously worked for a telco, OEM or analyst house.<br />
	- Good understanding of how software works, ideally having prior software development experience.<br />
	- Can quickly and eloquently turn ideas into words; and ability to craft attractive news headlines.<br />
	- Experienced in researching information online and having developed solid interviewing skills.<br />
	- Ability to break down a research project brief and develop a methodology emcompassing primary and secondary research.<br />
	- Comfortable working as part of a distributed team.<br />
	- Can work with a team to share, delegate or lead.<br />
	- Proactivity, self-discipline, determination, good finisher and attention to detail.<br />
	- Has led people or worked with people across geographies before.<br />
	- Has capacity for strategic thinking and connecting the dots.<br />
	- Ideally with a public voice (e.g. Twitter)</p>
<p>
	If you have a passion for mobile and for distilling market noise into market sense we &lsquo;d like to meet you.</p>
<p>
	Availability<br />
	Full-time, working a TechHub-style office as part of the distributed team at VisionMobile. Location will be preferably in London, otherwise Europe. Travelling is once a month or less.</p>
<p>
	Contact<br />
	If VisionMobile sounds like a place you&#39;d like to be for the next few years, send a short CV to jobs at visionmobile. Tell us a bit about yourself, why you want to join VisionMobile, and examples of your written work.</p>
]]></description>
